01:53:56.200 --> 01:53:59.870
I get a little bit anxious, a deep breath,

01:53:59.870 --> 01:54:02.960
or a few deep breaths are
tremendously effective

01:54:02.960 --> 01:54:05.140
in calming one down.

01:54:05.140 --> 01:54:10.140
And so, you can get a
transient disruption,

01:54:10.640 --> 01:54:15.640
but on the other hand, let's
take something like depression.

01:54:18.690 --> 01:54:21.800
I think it's, you can envision depression

01:54:21.800 --> 01:54:24.443
as activities sort of
going around in a circuit.

01:54:25.640 --> 01:54:29.330
And because it's continuous
in the nervous system,

01:54:29.330 --> 01:54:31.163
as signals keep repeating,

01:54:32.040 --> 01:54:35.870
they tend to get stronger
and they can get so strong,

01:54:35.870 --> 01:54:37.500
you can't break them.

01:54:37.500 --> 01:54:39.620
So, you can imagine the depression

01:54:39.620 --> 01:54:42.660
being something going on and on and on,

01:54:42.660 --> 01:54:44.060
and you can't break it.

01:54:44.060 --> 01:54:45.770
And so, we have trouble

01:54:45.770 --> 01:54:47.900
when we get for certain
levels of depression,

01:54:47.900 --> 01:54:50.310
I mean, all of us get
depressed at some point,

01:54:50.310 --> 01:54:53.640
but if it's not continuous,
it's not long lasting,

01:54:53.640 --> 01:54:55.350
we're able to break it.

01:54:55.350 --> 01:54:58.450
But if it's long lasting and
very deep, we can't break it.

01:54:58.450 --> 01:55:00.810
So, the question is how do we break it?

01:55:00.810 --> 01:55:03.300
Well, there are extreme
measures to break it.

01:55:03.300 --> 01:55:06.420
We could do electroconvulsive shock.

01:55:06.420 --> 01:55:08.090
We shock the whole brain.

01:55:08.090 --> 01:55:10.410
That's disrupting activity
in the whole brain.

01:55:10.410 --> 01:55:14.570
And when this circuit starts
to get back together again,

01:55:14.570 --> 01:55:15.710
it's been disruptive.

01:55:15.710 --> 01:55:17.590
And we know that the brain,

01:55:17.590 --> 01:55:20.520
when signals get disrupted a little bit,

01:55:20.520 --> 01:55:23.160
we can weaken the
connections and weakening

01:55:23.160 --> 01:55:24.063
the connections of this then

01:55:24.063 --> 01:55:26.690
in this circuit involved in depression,

01:55:26.690 --> 01:55:29.431
we may get some relief and
electroconvulsive shock

01:55:29.431 --> 01:55:33.410
does work for relieving
many kinds of depression.

01:55:33.410 --> 01:55:34.663
That's pretty heroic.

01:55:35.620 --> 01:55:39.930
Focal deep brain stimulation
does the same thing,

01:55:39.930 --> 01:55:43.690
but more localized or
transcranial stimulation.

01:55:43.690 --> 01:55:45.490
You're disrupting a network.

01:55:45.490 --> 01:55:47.610
And while it's getting back together,

01:55:47.610 --> 01:55:49.883
it may weaken some of the connections.

01:55:50.990 --> 01:55:55.133
If breathing is playing
some role in this circuit,

01:55:56.320 --> 01:56:00.800
and now, instead of doing
like a one second shock,

01:56:00.800 --> 01:56:04.540
I do 30 minutes of disruption
by doing slow breathing

01:56:04.540 --> 01:56:07.163
or other breathing practice,

01:56:07.997 --> 01:56:12.160
those circuits begin to
break down a little bit,

01:56:12.160 --> 01:56:13.260
and I get some relief.

01:56:13.260 --> 01:56:16.700
And if I continue to do
it before the circuit

01:56:16.700 --> 01:56:18.670
can then build back up again,

01:56:18.670 --> 01:56:20.750
I gradually can wear that circuit down.

01:56:20.750 --> 01:56:22.740
I sort of liken this,

01:56:22.740 --> 01:56:25.760
I tell people it's like
walking around on a dirt path.

01:56:25.760 --> 01:56:28.410
You build a rut, the rut gets so deep

01:56:28.410 --> 01:56:29.480
you can't get out of it.

01:56:29.480 --> 01:56:31.340
And what breathing is
doing is sort of filling

01:56:31.340 --> 01:56:32.940
in the right rut bit by bit

01:56:32.940 --> 01:56:35.750
to the point that you can
climb out of that rut.

01:56:35.750 --> 01:56:40.380
And that is because the breathing signal

01:56:40.380 --> 01:56:45.170
is playing some role in
the way the circuit works,

01:56:45.170 --> 01:56:47.060
and then when you disrupt that,

01:56:47.060 --> 01:56:49.720
the circuit gets a
little thrown off kilter,

01:56:49.720 --> 01:56:54.420
and as you know when
circuits get thrown off,

01:56:54.420 --> 01:56:57.630
the nervous system tries to
adjust in some way or another,

01:56:57.630 --> 01:57:00.260
and it turns out at least for breathing

01:57:01.100 --> 01:57:04.490
for some evolutionary reason,
or just by happenstance,

01:57:04.490 --> 01:57:06.793
it seems to improve
our emotional function,

01:57:06.793 --> 01:57:08.540
and our cognitive function.

01:57:08.540 --> 01:57:12.133
And we're very fortunate
that that's the case.

